                            <comment id="79045" author="bfaccini" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2014 21:32:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There has been only one failure of test_302 since mid-december (period where Patch-Set #8 of Change #7571 for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3726&quot; title=&quot;Adapt sanity-hsm to support MDSCOUNT &amp;gt;= 2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3726&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3726&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, with Change-Id: I6706571c92e4c3e978b2143dd5bdef4b73d2c1e2, has landed!), and after verification it has occured for a patch that needed to rebase (to be based on I6706571c92e4c3e978b2143dd5bdef4b73d2c1e2).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this confirms, what I earlier suspected/indicated, that change #7571 is also the fix for this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="73356" author="bfaccini" created="Thu, 12 Dec 2013 13:36:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure Oleg!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73326" author="green" created="Thu, 12 Dec 2013 00:35:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With 7571 now landed, please keep an eye on these failures to see if they went away?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73240" author="bfaccini" created="Tue, 10 Dec 2013 21:19:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like it is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3726&quot; title=&quot;Adapt sanity-hsm to support MDSCOUNT &amp;gt;= 2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3726&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3726&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; findings and could be fixed by Change #7571 starting with its patch-set #8, that still has&apos;nt been landed.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
